# 📌 About This Repository

This repository contains all the fundamental Java concepts required to build a strong foundation in **Data Structures and Algorithms (DSA)**.

It is structured in a step-by-step manner to help students:

- Strengthen Java basics
- Improve problem-solving skills
- Prepare for coding interviews
- Build logic from scratch

---

## 🧠 Topics Covered

### 1️⃣ Java Fundamentals
- Variables & Data Types
- Type Casting
- Operators
- Input & Output (Scanner)
- Comments

### 2️⃣ Conditional Statements
- if
- if-else
- else-if ladder
- switch case
- Ternary operator

### 3️⃣ Loops
- for loop
- while loop
- do-while loop
- Nested loops
- Pattern problems

### 4️⃣ Methods & Functions
- Method syntax
- Parameters vs Arguments
- Return types
- Method Overloading
- Call by Value in Java
- Recursion Basics

### 5️⃣ Strings
- String creation
- Important String methods
- StringBuilder
- Palindrome
- Anagram basics

### 6️⃣ Arrays
- 1D Arrays
- 2D Arrays
- Traversing arrays
- Reverse array
- Max/Min in array
- Prefix Sum (Basic intro)

### 7️⃣ OOP Basics
- Classes & Objects
- Constructors
- Encapsulation
- Inheritance
- Polymorphism
- Abstraction
- Interfaces

